# ============= ranks.d ==============
echo "x - extracting ranks.d (Text)"
sed 's/^X//' << 'SHAR_EOF' > ranks.d &&
X.BG
X.FN ranks
X.TL
XFunction to compute ranks from the dual (regression rankscore) process
X.DN
X.CS
Xranks(v, score="wilcoxon")
X.RA
X.AG v
Xregression quantile structure for the model of interest
X.OA
X.AG score
XThe score function desired.  Currently implemented score functions are
XWilcoxon, Normal, and Sign which are asymptotically optimal for the
Xlogistic, Gaussian and Laplace error models respectively.
X.RT
XThe function returns two components one is the ranks, the other is a
Xscale factor which is the L_2 norm of the score function.  All score
Xfunctions should be normalized to have mean zero.
X.SE
X.DT
X.SH REFERENCES
XGutenbrunner, C., J. Jureckova,  Koenker, R. and  Portnoy, S.(1993)
XTests of Linear Hypotheses  based on Regression Rank Scores",
XJournal of Nonparametric Statistics, (2), 307-331.
X.SA
XSee also rq, rrs.test
X.EX
Xranks(rq(stack.x,stack.loss))
X.KW regression quantiles, ranks, regression rankscores
X.WR
